<p>If you've spent any time looking into growth hormone peptides, you've probably run into CJC-1295. But there's a catch that trips people up: there are <strong>two versions</strong>.</p>

<p>CJC-1295 with DAC and CJC-1295 without DAC (sometimes called "mod GRF 1-29") are related compounds with very different behavior in the body. This guide covers the DAC version, the one that sticks around for days instead of minutes.</p>

